"```sql\nSELECT d.A2 AS district_name, COUNT(DISTINCT a.account_id) AS female_account_holders\nFROM account a\nJOIN disp dp ON a.account_id = dp.account_id\nJOIN client c ON dp.client_id = c.client_id\nJOIN district d ON a.district_id = d.district_id\nWHERE c.gender = 'F'\nGROUP BY d.A2\nORDER BY female_account_holders DESC\nLIMIT 9;\n```\n\nThis SQL query joins the necessary tables to count the number of distinct female account holders in each district, then orders the results in descending order and limits the output to the top nine districts."